    Scope and Contents
The Faculty Senate Master Campus  Physical Planning Committee (MCPPC) records (1980-) consists of agendas, minutes, university wide space allocation plans, PAC and Health &amp; Sciences Buildings, and memos to and from MCPPC regarding office and program relocations, meetings, space assignments and membership lists.  The MCPPC approves all revisions in the Campus Master Plan, acts as the advisory  and recommending body to the administration and solicits the university community's option on any potential major changes contemplated by the committee.  The MCPPC's overall charge is to match spaces and facilities with the needs of the schools and programs.  In 1979, the MCPPC succeeded the Building Committee, which was a division of the Council onUniversity Planning &amp; Development.  
  
